The paper discusses the use of deep ConvNets for end-to-end EEG analysis, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also focuses on the visualization of informative EEG features learned by the ConvNets, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential of deep ConvNets for EEG-based brain mapping, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
